g 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Market-Share-of-WooCommerce-Multilingual-Plugins-1.png 643w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<p>The total number of sites included in these statistics is 38,000+. The breakdown of active sites using each plugin is as follows:</p>\n<table width="453" align="center">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="296">Plugin</td>\n<td width="157">Total Sites</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="296">WooCommerce Multilingual</td>\n<td width="157">30,000+</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="296">WPGlobus</td>\n<td width="157">7,000+</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="296">WooCommerce Polylang Integration</td>\n<td width="157">1,000+</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>In today&#8217;s fast-paced world, having a multilingual eCommerce website is definitely one major tactic to penetrate new markets and expand your business. As demand grows for simple and efficient eCommerce solutions, WordPress, along with its many eCommerce themes and plugins, is the perfect choice for your next eCommerce project. Platforms like the WooCommerce plugin offer you all the features you’ll need to run your online store. For the next step—taking your shop and going multilingual—the leading solution is WooCommerce Multilingual plugin.</p>\n<p>After you have got all that set up and ready to go, it’s time to choose a stable, good WordPress Multilingual eCommerce theme. Below is a list of five that are worth noticing:</p>\n<h2>Top 5 WPML-Compatible eCommerce Themes</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href="#storefront">Storefront theme</a></li>\n<li><a href="#divi">Divi theme</a></li>\n<li><a href="#mayashop">MayaShop theme</a></li>\n<li><a href="#neighborhood">Neighborhood theme</a></li>\n<li><a href="#theretailer">The retailer theme</a></li>\n</ol>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 id="storefront">Storefront Theme</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/storefront-wpml-create-a-multilingual-shop/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft wp-image-854492" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-storefront-300x88.jpg" alt="wpml and storefront" width="650" height="191" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-storefront-300x88.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-storefront-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-storefront.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\n<p>Storefront provides a simple, solid foundation for your next eCommerce project. It comes with many display options and a wide variety of extensions. Its compatibility with many plugins makes it the best free ecommerce template to use. If you wish to expand your business and go global with a multilingual eCommerce website, Storefront and WPML is a brilliant choice.</p>\n<h3>What you will need</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.7 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.woothemes.com/storefront/">Storefront </a>(version 1.6.1 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Translating Storefront Theme</h3>\n<p>Check out this tutorial on how to <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/storefront-wpml-create-a-multilingual-shop/">create a multilingual shop using Storefront theme and WPML</a>.</p>\n<p>You can follow this step-by-step tutorial on <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">theme and plugins localization</a> to translate all Storefront theme elements using WPML.</p>\n<p>Check out this guide on how to use <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> to translate all strings generated by WooCommerce plugin.</p>\n<h3>Pros</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>It is free!</li>\n<li>Super fast, simple, and clean.</li>\n<li>Compatible with WPML and WooCommerce plugins/extensions</li>\n<li>Easy setup</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>You will need to purchase premium Storefront extensions to make any changes to the theme.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 id="divi">Divi Theme</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wpml.org/2015/05/build-a-multilingual-site-with-the-divi-theme/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft wp-image-854469" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-divi.jpg" alt="wpml and divi" width="650" height="191" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-divi.jpg 680w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-divi-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-divi-300x88.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\n<p>Divi is a multipurpose theme loaded with great graphics and a powerful page builder that has lots of eCommerce potential. Its compatibility with WPML makes it ideal for building your next or even first eCommerce website. <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/toolset-divi-integration/">Divi’s integration with Toolset</a>  will allow you to build sites using the drag-and-drop editor and fully control the layouts.</p>\n<h3>What you will need</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.7 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce M</a><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">ultilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.elegantthemes.com/gallery/divi/">Divi</a> (version 2.6.4 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Translating Divi Theme</h3>\n<p>Find our full tutorial on <a href="https://wpml.org/2015/05/build-a-multilingual-site-with-the-divi-theme/">building multilingual sites with Divi theme</a>.</p>\n<p>You can follow this step-by-step tutorial on <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">theme and plugins localization</a> to translate all Divi theme elements using WPML.</p>\n<p>Check out this guide on how to use <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> to translate all strings generated by WooCommerce plugin.</p>\n<h3>Pros</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Ideal for non-technical users.</li>\n<li>Provides neat documentation.</li>\n<li>A powerful drag-and-drop page builder.</li>\n<li>Compatible with WPML, WooCommerce, MailChimp, and Google Maps.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Tons of options that may overwhelm you.</li>\n<li>Not the optimal option for developers.</li>\n<li>You may encounter an unpleasant experience when switching from Divi to another theme as Divi&#8217;s page builder generates short codes which will be broken links if you chose to activate a different theme.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 id="mayashop">MayaShop Theme</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-mayashop-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft wp-image-854515" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-300x88.jpg" alt="wpml and mayashop" width="650" height="191" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-300x88.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\n<p>MayaShop is loaded with layout options, skins, colors and fonts, enabling you to craft a highly customizable eCommerce theme. It is 100% compatible with WPML, which makes it a smart pick for building your eCommerce website. It is coupled with neat and organized documentation to guide you through your build.</p>\n<h3>What you will need</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.7 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/mayashop-a-flexible-responsive-ecommerce-theme/2189918?s_rank=10">MayaShop</a> (version 2.9.3 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Translating MayaShop Theme</h3>\n<p>Check our complete tutorial on how to <a href="https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-mayashop-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank">Translate MayaShop theme using WPML</a>.</p>\n<p>You can follow this step-by-step tutorial on <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">theme and plugins localization</a> to translate all MayaShop theme elements using WPML.</p>\n<p>Check out this guide on how to use <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> to translate all strings generated by WooCommerce plugin.</p>\n<h3>Pros</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Highly customizable.</li>\n<li>Compatible with WPML, Jigoshop, and WooCommerce plugin.</li>\n<li>Great documentation for beginners.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Paid theme</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 id="neighborhood">Neighborhood Theme</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-neighborhood-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft wp-image-854541" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-neighborhood-1-300x88.jpg" alt="wpml and neighborhood" width="650" height="191" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-neighborhood-1-300x88.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-neighborhood-1-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-neighborhood-1.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\n<p>Neighborhood is a responsive, multipurpose shop theme that provides an awesome drag-and-drop page builder and an unlimited number of layouts and colors, which will make your eCommerce site stand out. The Neighborhood theme is fully compatible with WPML, making building your next eCommerce website an effortless experience.</p>\n<h3>What you will need</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.7 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/neighborhood-responsive-multipurpose-shop-theme/5086341">Neighborhood theme</a> (version 2.05 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Translating Neighborhood Theme</h3>\n<p>Check out this tutorial on how to <a href="https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-neighborhood-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank">Translate Neighborhood Theme Using WPML</a></p>\n<p>You can follow this step-by-step tutorial on <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">theme and plugins localization</a> to translate all Neighborhood theme elements using WPML.</p>\n<p>Check out this guide on how to use <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> to translate all strings generated by WooCommerce plugin.</p>\n<h3>Pros</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Simple drag-and-drop page builder.</li>\n<li>Extremely customizable.</li>\n<li>Compatible with WPML and WooCommerce.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Paid theme</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 id="theretailer">The Retailer Theme</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wpml.org/2016/03/translate-retailer-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft wp-image-854562" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-the-retailer-300x88.jpg" alt="wpml and the retailer" width="650" height="191" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-the-retailer-300x88.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-the-retailer-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-the-retailer.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Retailer theme comes with many theme options, lots of pre-built layouts and tons of other features. It is fully compatible with WooCommrce which make it a good choice for building a clean and professional online store. Its integration with WPML allows you to translate all the theme elements effortlessly.</span></p>\n<h3>What you will need</h3>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">A recent version of </span><a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/"><span style="font-weight: 400">WPML</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> (version 3.3.7 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, Media translation add-ons and </span><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/"><span style="font-weight: 400">WooCommerce multilingual</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> plugin.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400"><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/the-retailer-responsive-wordpress-theme/4287447"><span style="font-weight: 400">The Retailer</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> theme (version 2.4.4 or above)</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/"><span style="font-weight: 400">WooCommerce</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> (version 2.5.3 or above)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Translate The Retailer Theme</h3>\n<p>Check out this tutorial on how to <a href="https://wpml.org/2016/03/translate-retailer-theme-using-wpml/" target="_blank">Translate The Retailer Theme using WPML</a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400">You can follow this step-by-step tutorial on </span><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/"><span style="font-weight: 400">theme and plugins localization</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> to translate all Storefront theme elements using WPML. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Check this guide on how to use </span><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/"><span style="font-weight: 400">WooCommerce Multilingual</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">  to translate all strings generated by WooCommerce plugin.</span></p>\n<h3>Pros</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Highly  customizable.</li>\n<li>Compatible with WPML and WooCommerce.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Cons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Paid theme</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>Choosing the right theme and plugins to run your WordPress eCommerce online store might be tricky, as the market has got an enormous number of choices. Choosing an eCommerce theme that is fully compatible with WooCommerce and WooCommerce Multilingual plugins will ensure you an effortless experience in building your eCommerce online store.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Resourses<br />\n<a href="https://www.sellwithwp.com/wordpress-ecommerce-plugin-statistics/">https://www.sellwithwp.com/wordpress-ecommerce-plugin-statistics/</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://solutiondots.com/blog/wordpress-multilingual-plugins.html">http://solutiondots.com/blog/wordpress-multilingual-plugins.html</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://hbr.org/2012/08/speak-to-global-customers-in-t/">https://hbr.org/2012/08/speak-to-global-customers-in-t/</a></p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=qI2etlB-uk8:w3_4wTi_iW4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/qI2etlB-uk8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/top-5-wpml-compatible-ecommerce-themes/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/top-5-wpml-compatible-ecommerce-themes/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"Translate MayaShop Theme Using WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/FOtZGlS4wj4/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-mayashop-theme-using-wpml/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 05 Apr 2016 12:10:59 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Compatibility";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=853321";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:356:"Introduction MayaShop is a highly customizable eCommerce theme with several layout options, skins, colors, and fonts. It is 100% compatible with WPML, making it a smart pick for building your eCommerce website. Further, the theme has neat and organized documentation to guide you through your build process. What you will need A recent version of [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13898:"<h3><img class="alignnone wp-image-858994 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-1.jpg" alt="wpml and mayashop" width="680" height="200" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-1.jpg 680w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-1-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wpml-and-mayashop-1-300x88.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></h3>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Introduction</span></h3>\n<p>MayaShop is a highly customizable eCommerce theme with several layout options, skins, colors, and fonts. It is 100% compatible with WPML, making it a smart pick for building your eCommerce website. Further, the theme has neat and organized documentation to guide you through your build process.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">What you will need</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.6 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons, and the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/mayashop-a-flexible-responsive-ecommerce-theme/2189918?s_rank=10">MayaShop</a> (version 2.9.3 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Essential resources</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://docs.yithemes.com/maya/">MayaShop documentation</a> has detailed setup instructions for MayaShop.</li>\n<li>WPML’s <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> will help you set up WPML in a few minutes. You might want to refer to some of its subtopics later, such as <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a> and <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/string-translation/">String Translation</a>. We recommend you keep this guide open while following this tutorial.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Contents</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Getting started</li>\n<li>Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</li>\n<li>Translating menus</li>\n<li>Translating theme text and other strings</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Getting started</span></h3>\n<p>Perform the following steps to get started:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MayaShop theme and activate it.</li>\n<li>Install and activate the core WPML plugins (WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, WPML Translation Management, and WPML Media Translation), and then other WPML plugins that may depend on them.</li>\n<li>Set up WPML from WPML <strong>&gt;</strong> See the WPML <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> for complete information; the initial, simple three-step setup process is self-explanatory, prompting you to choose your default language, a set of active languages, and a language selector.<br />\n(For starters, it is recommended to choose the footer language selector; you can change this later.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</span></h3>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6"> Translate pages</span></h3>\n<p>To translate pages and posts, perform the following steps:</p>\n<p>Navigate to Pages or Posts on the WordPress dashboard and click on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-853332" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Plus-icon.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" /> icon to add the translated content in the secondary language.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853325" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1-300x135.png" alt="Page translation 1" width="450" height="203" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1-768x347.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1-1024x462.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Page-translation-1.png 1336w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></a></p>\n<p>Click on the “Copy content from” button to get a copy of the content in your default language, and then add the translated content and click on the “Publish” button.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853328" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2-300x139.png" alt="page translation 2" width="450" height="209" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2-300x139.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2-150x70.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2-768x356.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2-1024x475.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/page-translation-2.png 1331w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></a></p>\n<p>Perform the same steps to translate posts.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translate custom post types (portfolio)</span></h3>\n<p>MayaShop theme has many custom post types (Portfolio, Testimonials, FAQs, and Gallery). As an example, we will translate the custom post type “Portfolio” and the custom taxonomy “Portfolio Categories”; these are preset to be translated by the language configuration file created for MayaShop theme.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to “Portfolio” on your WordPress dashboard and click on the “Add New” button; ensure that the language switcher in the main admin bar is set to your default language and then click on ‘Publish’. Now you can click on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-853332" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Plus-icon.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" /> icon in the language meta box.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853335" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1-300x148.png" alt="portfolio translation 1" width="450" height="222" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1-300x148.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1-150x74.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1-768x380.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1-1024x506.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-1.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="2">\n<li>Click on the “Copy content from” button on the language meta box on the right, add the translated text, and click on the “Publish” button; you will notice that the language switcher in the admin bar is now set to the secondary language.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853341" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2-300x148.png" alt="portfolio translation 2" width="540" height="267" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2-300x148.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2-150x74.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2-768x380.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2-1024x506.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-translation-2.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px" /></a></p>\n<p>Perform the same steps to translate the other custom post types.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translate custom taxonomies (Faq Categories)</span></h3>\n<p>To translate the custom taxonomies follow the steps below:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML <strong>&gt;&gt; </strong>Taxonomy Translation</li>\n<li>Select “Faq Categories” from the “Select the taxonomy to translate drop” down menu</li>\n<li>Click on the “translate” to add the custom taxonomy translation by filling in the required fields, and then click “OK.”</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853344" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation-300x142.png" alt="faq category translation" width="450" height="213" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation-300x142.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation-150x71.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation-768x363.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation-1024x484.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-category-translation.png 1581w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating menus </span></h3>\n<p>With WPML, you can easily synchronize your language menu. For more information, please check our full <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/translating-menus/">translating menus</a> tutorial.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating theme text and other strings</span></h3>\n<p>Theme strings can be scanned and registered for translation on the string translation screen. Read more about <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a>.</p>\n<p>Perform the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML &gt; Theme and plugin localization</li>\n<li>Click on the “Scan the theme for strings” button; this will register the theme texts for translation on the string translation screen.</li>\n<li>Navigate to WPML &gt; String translation</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Strings can be filtered in the following manner:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select the strings required to be displayed (Translation complete, Translation needed, Waiting for translator).</li>\n<li>Select a specific text domain.</li>\n<li>Search for a specific string by typing it in the “Search for:” field and click on the “Search” button.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start="4">\n<li>Click on “translations” and add your translated text.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Enable the “Translation is complete” checkbox and click “Save.”</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-853360" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation-300x135.png" alt="string translation" width="450" height="203" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation-768x346.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation-1024x461.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/string-translation.png 1341w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></a></p>\n<p>To translate the theme options, choose “admin_text_yiw_theme_options_maya” string domain on the string translation screen.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Getting help</span></h3>\n<p>If you need help while using WPML withMayaShop theme, visit our <a href="https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/">technical forum</a>.</p>\n<p>Before posting your concerns, we recommend that you review the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Ensure that you have the latest versions of the theme and WPML plugins and that they are all activated. These include WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, and WPML Translation Management.</li>\n<li>Confirm that your issue does not arise when the WPML plugins are deactivated but <em>does</em> arise when only the core WPML plugins are activated. In other words, ensure that it is an issue of compatibility between the MayaShop theme and WPML. Otherwise, MayaShop support can offer better assistance.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Conclusion</span></h3>\n<p>MayaShop is a flexible and responsive eCommerce theme that will enable you to create an attractive online store. Its integration with WPML will allow you to translate all the theme elements easily.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=FOtZGlS4wj4:AlBh0yos2es:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/FOtZGlS4wj4" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-mayashop-theme-using-wpml/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-mayashop-theme-using-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"Translate Neighborhood  Theme Using WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/GWZQPDgIEH8/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-neighborhood-theme-using-wpml/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 01 Apr 2016 09:02:27 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=849123";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:384:"Introduction Neighborhood is a responsive multi-purpose shop theme that provides a drag-and-drop page builder and an unlimited number of layouts and colors that will enable your eCommerce site to stand out. Neighborhood theme is fully compatible with WPML, which makes building your next multilingual eCommerce website an enjoyable experience. What you need A recent version [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19109:"<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Introduction</span></h3>\n<p>Neighborhood is a responsive multi-purpose shop theme that provides a drag-and-drop page builder and an unlimited number of layouts and colors that will enable your eCommerce site to stand out. Neighborhood theme is fully compatible with WPML, which makes building your next multilingual eCommerce website an enjoyable experience.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">What you need</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.6 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, Media Translation add-ons, and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/neighborhood-responsive-multipurpose-shop-theme/5086341">Neighborhood Theme</a> (version 3.2.5 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.5 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Essential resources</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>WPML’s <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> will help you to set up WPML in only a few minutes. You will want to refer later to some of its subtopics, such as <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a> and <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/string-translation/">String Translation</a>. In addition, we suggest you refer to the <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> We recommend that these guides remain open while you follow this tutorial.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Content</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Translating the Home page (Shop page).</li>\n<li>Translating products and product categories.</li>\n<li>Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</li>\n<li>Translating menus.</li>\n<li>Translating theme text and other strings.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Getting started</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and activate Neighborhood.</li>\n<li>Install and activate the WPML plugins (WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, WPML Translation Management, and WPML Media)</li>\n<li>Install and activate WooCommerce Multilingual.</li>\n<li>Set up WPML from WPML &gt;&gt; Languages. Refer to our <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">WPML Getting Started Guide</a> for complete reference.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating the Home page (Shop page)</span></h3>\n<p>Neighborhood theme comes with “Swift Page Builder,” which we will use in this tutorial to create our shop page.</p>\n<p>Note the following:</p>\n<p>The “Swift Page Builder” is a page layout builder that allows you to design and modify the layout as well as add functionality inside a single page and view from within the admin of that page.</p>\n<p>In addition, please note that the WooCommerce plugin creates its own shop page.</p>\n<p>You can perform the following steps to translate any page created with the “Swift Page Builder.”</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to WordPress dashboard.</li>\n<li>Click on Pages, Add new.</li>\n<li>Name the page “Shop.”</li>\n<li>Click the “Swift Page Builder” button.</li>\n<li>Click “Choose Elements.”</li>\n<li>Click “Products.” This will show all the products that you have created. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849126" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page-300x135.png" alt="Create the shop page" width="530" height="238" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page-150x67.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page-768x345.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page-1024x461.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Create-the-shop-page.png 1336w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<p>To translate the shop page elements, navigate to “Pages” in WordPress dashboard, which shows columns for each active language and a <img class="alignnone wp-image-849129" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Plus-icon-1.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" />  icon (to add a translation) or a <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-849131" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Pen-icon-1.png" alt="Pencil" width="17" height="16" />  icon (to edit a translation) next to each page.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Add the translation for your “Shop” page by clicking on the <img class="alignnone wp-image-849129" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Plus-icon-1.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" /> icon.</li>\n<li>On the right, you will see the language metabox. Click on “copy content from English” to copy the content created using the “Swift Page Builder.”</li>\n<li>Now add the translation to your secondary language shop page and click the “Publish” button. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849135" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2-300x127.png" alt="Translate shop page-2" width="530" height="224" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2-300x127.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2-150x63.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2-768x324.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2-1024x432.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-shop-page-2.png 1326w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating products and product categories</span></h3>\n<p>You can translate products by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to WPML &gt;&gt; WooCommerce Multilingual.</li>\n<li>Navigate to the “Products” tab.</li>\n<li>Click on the “Edit translation” link. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849138" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products-300x135.png" alt="Translate products" width="530" height="238" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products-150x67.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products-768x344.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products-1024x459.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Translate-products.png 1327w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="4">\n<li>Add the translated content to the product and click the “Save” button, as shown in the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849141" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2-300x137.png" alt="translate products 2" width="531" height="243" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2-300x137.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2-150x69.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2-768x351.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2-1024x469.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-products-2.png 1331w" sizes="(max-width: 531px) 100vw, 531px" /></a></p>\n<p>Product categories can be translated by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to WPML &gt;&gt; WooCommerce Multilingual.</li>\n<li>Navigate to the “Product Categories” tab.</li>\n<li>Click on the “translate” link, add the translated content, and click the “Save” button. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849149" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-300x131.png" alt="translate product categories" width="530" height="231" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-300x131.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-150x65.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-768x335.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1024x447.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories.png 1334w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</span></h3>\n<p>Translating pages and posts can be accomplished by navigating to Pages or Posts on the WordPress dashboard and clicking on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-842486" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Plus-icon.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" /> icon to add the translated content to the secondary language.</p>\n<p>Neighborhood theme comes with many custom post types (Portfolio, Team, Clients, Testimonials, Jobs, and FAQs). As an example, we will translate the custom post type “Portfolio” and the custom taxonomy “Portfolio Categories. These are preset to be translated by the language configuration file that we have created for the Neighborhood theme.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translate portfolio</span></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to “Portfolio” in your WordPress dashboard and click the “Add New” button, Ensure that the main admin bar language switcher is set to be your default language, then click “Publish.” You can then click on the <img src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Plus-icon-1.png" alt="Plus icon" width="16" height="16" /> icon in the language metabox.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849154" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-300x144.png" alt="translate portfolio item" width="530" height="254" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-300x144.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-150x72.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-768x368.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-1024x491.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item.png 1323w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="2">\n<li>You can next add the translated text and click the “Publish” button. You will notice that the admin bar language switcher shows the secondary language. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849173" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2-300x143.png" alt="translate portfolio item 2" width="530" height="253" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2-300x143.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2-150x72.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2-768x367.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2-1024x489.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-portfolio-item-2.png 1335w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6"><strong>Translate portfolio categories</strong></span></h3>\n<p>To translate custom taxonomies, follow these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to WPML <strong>&gt;&gt; </strong>Taxonomy Translation.</li>\n<li>Select “Portfolio Categories” from the “Select the taxonomy to translate” drop-down menu.</li>\n<li>Click on “translate,” complete the required fields, and click “OK” to add the custom taxonomy translation, as illustrated in the following.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849176" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1-300x131.png" alt="translate product categories" width="530" height="231" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1-300x131.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1-150x65.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1-768x335.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1-1024x447.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/translate-product-categories-1.png 1334w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating menus</span></h3>\n<p>Using WPML, you can easily synchronize your language menus. For more information, please refer to the full <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/translating-menus/">translating menus</a> tutorial.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating theme text and other strings</span></h3>\n<p>Theme strings can be scanned and registered for translation on the string translation screen. Read more about <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a>.</p>\n<p>This can be done by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML <strong>&gt;&gt; </strong>Theme and plugin localization</li>\n<li>Click the “Scan the theme for strings” button. This will register the theme texts for translation on the string translation screen. See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849181" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings-300x129.png" alt="scan the theme for strings" width="530" height="227" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings-300x129.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings-150x64.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings-768x329.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings-1024x439.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/scan-the-theme-for-strings.png 1331w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="3">\n<li>Navigate to WPML &gt;&gt; String translation. You can filter the strings by means of “translation needed” to identify those strings that are missing translations or select a specific text domain. You also can search for a specific string by typing it in the “Search for” field, then clicking the “Search” button. Click on “translations” and add your translated text. Select the “Translation is complete” option and click “Save.” See the image that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-849188" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1-300x135.png" alt="string translation" width="530" height="239" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1-768x346.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1-1024x462.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/string-translation-1.png 1339w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<p>Note that translating the theme options can be accomplished by navigating to WPML &gt;&gt; String translation and searching for the strings within the domain “admin_texts_sf_neighborhood_options.”</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Getting help</span></h3>\n<p>If you need help using WPML with Neighborhood theme, please head over to our <a href="https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/">technical forum</a>.</p>\n<p>Before posting your concerns, we recommend that you review the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Ensure you have the latest versions of the theme and WPML plugins, and that they are all activated. These include WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, and WPML Translation Management.</li>\n<li>Confirm that your issue does not arise when the WPML plugins are deactivated, but <em>does</em> arise when only the core WPML plugins are activated. In other words, ensure that it is an issue of compatibility of Neighborhood with WPML. Otherwise, Bridge support can offer better assistance.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6"><strong>Conclusion</strong></span></h3>\n<p>Neighborhood theme includes many features that will allow you to build a clean and professional eCommerce website. Its integration with WPML provides an easy interface to make your online store multilingual.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GWZQPDgIEH8:OtKFI7HNY_E:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/GWZQPDgIEH8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-neighborhood-theme-using-wpml/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/translate-neighborhood-theme-using-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"WPML 3.3.7 Released – WordPress 4.5 Compatible, Faster, More Stable";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/4S-kpkuMtok/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-3-3-7-released-wordpress-4-5-compatible-faster-stable/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 30 Mar 2016 10:03:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WPML versions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=848457";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:339:"WPML 3.3.7 is a maintenance update, which handles all required updates for the last few weeks. Since WordPress 4.5 is coming soon, you should definitely update to WPML 3.3.7 and be prepared. The full list of changes appears in WPML 3.3.7 beta announcement. Since the announcement, we completed our internal QA (yes, it takes that [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Amir";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3644:"<p>WPML 3.3.7 is a maintenance update, which handles all required updates for the last few weeks. Since WordPress 4.5 is coming soon, you should definitely update to WPML 3.3.7 and be prepared.</p>\n<p>The full list of changes appears in <a href="https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-compatibility-release-wordpress-4-5/">WPML 3.3.7 beta announcement</a>. Since the announcement, we completed our internal QA (yes, it takes that long) and corrected a number of additional glitches.</p>\n<p>We are currently running WPML 3.3.7 on our sites.</p>\n<h2>Coming soon to WPML</h2>\n<p>You&#8217;re probably aware of other development work that we&#8217;re doing, so let me give a quick update on the progress.</p>\n<p>The next release of WPML will include a complete redesign for much of the user interface. This change will give the biggest improvements to the Translation Editor. If you are using WooCommerce Multilingual, you will see the entire change. We&#8217;ve re-engineered the translation workflow for WooCommerce products, making it a lot easier for you to run multilingual e-commerce shops. Even without WooCommerce Multilingual, you will notice a streamlined translation process in WPML.</p>\n<p>Also coming to WPML 3.4 is complete compatibility with PHP7. You may have heard that PHP7 gets to x3 faster than PHP 5.6. We&#8217;re looking forward to updating our own servers to PHP 7 and enjoying this boost in performance. Remember that all the plugins that you use need to be compatible with PHP 7 before you upgrade.</p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s not all. Other major features in WPML&#8217;s pipe include a much enhanced language switcher, with many more options and full compatibility with modern CSS frameworks. We&#8217;re completing the taxonomy terms translation and translation for links in custom fields and strings.</p>\n<p>To get you new features faster, we&#8217;re separating them into different releases. WPML 3.4 will include the updated UI (both in WPML and in WooCommerce Multilingual). The other new features will follow in the next version(s).</p>\n<h2>Download and give us feedback</h2>\n<p>First, remember to backup your site before updating. We backup our site and test updates before we update ANYTHING (any plugin, the theme or WordPress). This release of WPML has gone through weeks of testing by dozens of people, but it&#8217;s still nicer to find glitches on a test site and not on a production server.</p>\n<p>Then, update all of WPML components. There is dependency between WPML core and its add-ons. If you update one, update all.</p>\n<p>The best way to update WPML is from the WordPress admin. Register your site (you can register all your sites, we don&#8217;t limit) to get automated updates. Alternatively, you can always download WPML manually from <a href="https://wpml.org/account/">your account</a>.</p>\n<p>Leave your comments to give us your feedback, ask questions or make suggestions. We&#8217;ll get back to you.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4S-kpkuMtok:28j_84-sFO8:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/4S-kpkuMtok" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-3-3-7-released-wordpress-4-5-compatible-faster-stable/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"14";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-3-3-7-released-wordpress-4-5-compatible-faster-stable/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"Translate The Retailer Theme using WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/O2mEE9jBm7k/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/translate-retailer-theme-using-wpml/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 29 Mar 2016 15:00:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Compatibility";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=845857";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:358:"Introduction The Retailer theme comes with many theme options, pre-built layouts, demo content and other features. It is fully compatible with WooCommerce, which make it a good choice for building a clean and professional online store. Its integration with WPML allows you to translate all theme and shop elements effortlessly. What you will need A [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13500:"<h3><img class="alignnone wp-image-858999 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wpml-and-the-retailer.jpg" alt="wpml and the retailer" width="680" height="200" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wpml-and-the-retailer.jpg 680w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wpml-and-the-retailer-150x44.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wpml-and-the-retailer-300x88.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></h3>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Introduction</span></h3>\n<p>The Retailer theme comes with many theme options, pre-built layouts, demo content and other features. It is fully compatible with WooCommerce, which make it a good choice for building a clean and professional online store. Its integration with WPML allows you to translate all theme and shop elements effortlessly.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">What you will need</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.6 or above), including String Translation, Translation Management, Media Translation add-ons, and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce multilingual</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/the-retailer-responsive-wordpress-theme/4287447">The Retailer</a> theme (version 2.4.4 or above)</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/">WooCommerce</a> (version 2.5.5 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Essential resources</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>WPML’s <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> will assist you in setting up WPML in only a few minutes. Later, you may want to refer to some of its subtopics, such as <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a> and <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/string-translation/">String Translation</a>. In addition, review the <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">Woocommerce Multilingual</a> We recommend you keep these guides open while following this tutorial.</li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400"><a href="http://support.getbowtied.com/hc/en-us/categories/200102021-The-Retailer" target="_blank">The Retailer theme documentation</a></span><span style="font-weight: 400"> has a step by step guide on how to set it up.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Content</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Translating the home page(shop page)</li>\n<li>Translating products and product categories</li>\n<li>Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</li>\n<li>Translating menus</li>\n<li>Translating theme text and other strings</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Getting started</span></h3>\n<p>Follow these main steps to get started:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install The Retailer theme and activate it.</li>\n<li>Install and activate the core WPML plugins (WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, WPML Translation Management, WPML Media Translation), and then other WPML plugins that may depend on them.</li>\n<li>Set up WPML from WPML &gt;&gt; See our WPML <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> for a complete reference. Note, however, that the initial three-step setup is self-explanatory, asking you to choose your default language, a set of active languages, and a language selector. (To begin, choose the footer language selector. You can change this later.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For this tutorial, we use the demo content provided by The Retailer theme. You can import this content by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>From your WordPress dashboard, navigate to “The Retailer.”</li>\n<li>Click on “Demo.”</li>\n<li>Click on the “Install” button.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845859" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content-300x145.png" alt="Install demo content" width="530" height="256" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content-300x145.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content-150x73.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content-768x371.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content-1024x495.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Install-demo-content.png 1319w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating the home page (shop page)</span></h3>\n<p>The demo homepage installed by “The Retailer” theme is built using the <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/visual-composer-page-builder-for-wordpress/242431">Visual Composer</a> (VC) page builder.</p>\n<p>To translate the home page or any other page created with VC follow these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to “Pages.”</li>\n<li>Find the home page and click the icon to add the translation.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845860" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1-300x134.png" alt="Home page transaltion-1" width="530" height="236" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1-300x134.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1-150x67.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1-768x342.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1-1024x456.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-transaltion-1.png 1339w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="3">\n<li>Click on the “copy content from English” button found on the language metabox to copy your content to the secondary language home page.</li>\n<li>Click the “BACKEND EDITOR” option.</li>\n<li>Add the translated text to the page title and the different VC elements.</li>\n<li>Publish the page. (Refer to the illustration that follows.)</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845863" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2-300x142.png" alt="Home page tranaslation-2" width="530" height="251" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2-300x142.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2-150x71.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2-768x364.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2-1024x485.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Home-page-tranaslation-2.png 1331w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating products and product categories</span></h3>\n<p>You can translate products and product categories using WooCommerce Multilingual. Please refer to our full tutorial on using <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/">WooCommerce Multilingual</a>.</p>\n<p>Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</p>\n<p>Translating pages, posts, and the custom post types (Portfolio) can be achieved by navigating to Pages or Posts on the WordPress dashboard and clicking the  icon to add the translated content to the secondary language in the same manner we translated the home page.</p>\n<p>To translate custom taxonomies, follow these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML &gt;&gt; Taxonomy Translation.</li>\n<li>Select “Portfolio Categories” from the “Select the taxonomy to translate drop down” menu.</li>\n<li>Click on “translate,” complete the required fields, and click “OK” to add the custom taxonomy translation, as illustrated that follows.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845866" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation-300x136.png" alt="portofolio category translation" width="530" height="240" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation-300x136.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation-768x347.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation-1024x463.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portofolio-category-translation.png 1333w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating menus</span></h3>\n<p>Using WPML, you can easily synchronize menus between languages. For more information, please refer to our complete <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/translating-menus/">translating menus</a> tutorial.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Translating theme text and other strings</span></h3>\n<p>Theme strings can be scanned and registered for translation on the string translation screen. Read more about this here: <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a>.</p>\n<p>This can be accomplished by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML &gt;&gt; Click on Theme and plugin localization</li>\n<li>Click on the “Scan the theme for strings” button. This will register the theme texts for translation on the string translation screen. (Please refer to the illustration that follows.)</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845868" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1-300x132.png" alt="Scan theme for strings" width="530" height="233" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1-300x132.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1-150x66.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1-768x338.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1-1024x450.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Scan-theme-for-strings-1.png 1346w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="3">\n<li>Next, navigate to WPML &gt;&gt; String translation.</li>\n</ol>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">Strings can be filtered by:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select the strings to display (Translation complete, Translation needed, Waiting for translator).</li>\n<li>Select a specific text domain.</li>\n<li>Search for a specific string by typing it in the “search for” field and clicking the “search” button.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start="4">\n<li>Click on “translations” and add your translated text. Then choose the “Translation is complete” option and click “Save.” (Refer to the illustration that follows.)</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-845870" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation-300x135.png" alt="String translation" width="530" height="239" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation-300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation-768x346.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation-1024x462.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/String-translation.png 1349w" sizes="(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px" /></a></p>\n<p>Note that translating admin texts/theme options can be achieved by choosing the “admin_text_theme_mods_theretailer” and “getbowtied” string domains on the string translation screen.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #3e9fb6">Conclusion</span></h3>\n<p>The Retailer is a simple yet powerful eCommerce theme that enables you to create an attractive online store. Its integration with WPML allows you to translate all theme elements smoothly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=O2mEE9jBm7k:Z_ElXQm5nus:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/O2mEE9jBm7k" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/translate-retailer-theme-using-wpml/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/translate-retailer-theme-using-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"WPML compatibility release for WordPress 4.5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/4aaiwkl2VLg/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-compatibility-release-wordpress-4-5/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 17 Mar 2016 15:05:05 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WPML versions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=838939";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:337:"We are working to release an update for WPML (and its add-ons plugins) to address some compatibility issues with WordPress 4.5. WordPress 4.5 brings several changes in its API, changes which need to be addressed and which require holding the development of WPML 3.4 (more about WPML 3.4 in the next posts). Of course, some bug [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Andrea";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5848:"<p>We are working to release an update for WPML (and its add-ons plugins) to address some compatibility issues with WordPress 4.5.</p>\n<p>WordPress 4.5 brings several changes in its API, changes which need to be addressed and which require holding the development of WPML 3.4 (more about WPML 3.4 in the next posts).</p>\n<p>Of course, some bug fixes not related to WordPress 4.5 also slipped in, as they occurred during the development of WPML 3.4.</p>\n<p>We are currently under full QA, which usually takes several days, but you can start using our <strong>beta version</strong> right now. If you do so, please share your feedback or questions in our <a href="https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/">support forum</a>.</p>\n<h2>WP 4.5 Fixes</h2>\n<p>As for WordPress 4.5 compatibility, here&#8217;s a list of what we have worked with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>WPML Core 3.3.7</strong>: fixed compatibility issues with terms editing functionalities</li>\n<li><strong>WPML Translation Management 2.1.6</strong>: replaced use of deprecated function `get_currentuserinfo`</li>\n<li><strong>WPML String Translation 2.3.7</strong>: fixed filtering rewrite rules for WP 4.5 when the rules are cleared</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Other relevant changes in WPML 3.3.7</h2>\n<p>You can find the full <strong>changelog.md</strong> in each plugin&#8217;s folder.</p>\n<h3><strong>WPML Core 3.3.7</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed some issues with post synchronization (&#8220;Copy publishing date&#8221; option and post date synchronisation).</li>\n<li>Fixed several WP SEO compatibility issues with sitemaps generation, missing trailing slashes, taxonomies, and &#8220;Adjust IDs for multilingual functionality&#8221; being randomly disabled</li>\n<li>Fixed unexpected browser redirection on root page</li>\n<li>When the blog page is deleted and then re-translated, it is now possible to set the blog page in Settings &gt; Reading</li>\n<li>Improved sitepress.js to use var when declaring variables, so as to allow minification and combination of scripts in strict mode</li>\n<li>Show language switcher if CPT is set to do nothing</li>\n<li>`wp_get_archives` now works for any custom post type</li>\n<li>Fixed notices when updating to the latest version with browser redirection activated.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Performances</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Removed non-translators cache from options.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Features</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Auto-disconnect duplicates when they are edited and only if there are changes.</li>\n<li>Increased the accepted length of &#8220;Default Locale&#8221; and &#8220;Tag&#8221; in the languages table, so as to allow variations such as &#8220;de_DE_formal&#8221;</li>\n<li>Hide system fields when displaying custom fields and terms meta in &#8220;Multilingual Content Setup&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Compatibility</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>WP SEO user meta fields are now translatable with WPML String Translation</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>WPML String Translation 2.3.7</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed issue with theme scanned on each access to WPML &gt; Plugin and theme localization</li>\n<li>Fixed error when scanning themes/plugins for strings on localhost on Windows</li>\n<li>Fixed filtering of translation jobs when selecting &#8220;From language&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Features</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Author biographical info is now translatable in string translation</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>WPML Translation Management 2.1.6</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed issue where translated XLIFFs with &#8216;0&#8217; (zero) as content were not accepted from Translation Management</li>\n<li>Fixed `Fatal error: Uncaught exception &#8216;InvalidArgumentException&#8217; with message &#8216;Tried to load a string filter for a non-existent language&#8217;`</li>\n<li>Added option to disconnect multiple duplicates (bulk mode) in TM Basket before sending for translation.</li>\n<li>Fixed issue with incorrect redirections after translation save/update and wrong post/page edit links.</li>\n<li>Reduce the number of DB queries on listing pages.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Features</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Hide system fields when displaying custom fields and terms meta</li>\n<li>Added external-file in XLIFF files, to allow third party services to access the original URL.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>WPML Media Translation 2.1.20</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed language filter issue in Media Library section.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>CMS NAV 1.4.18</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>`$post-&gt;ancestors` is a read-only field and should not be set</li>\n<li>Fixed bug occurring when the &#8220;auto-save&#8221; action was running, and causing some CMS-NAV loss data during post editing</li>\n<li>Fixed issue with pages&#8217; order not being respected</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Gravity Forms Multilingual 1.3.8</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Fixes</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed issue when a field is removed from a form: the related strings are now removed</li>\n<li>Previous and next buttons are now fully translatable</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4aaiwkl2VLg:jwOkBtCk6Ss:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/4aaiwkl2VLg" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-compatibility-release-wordpress-4-5/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"16";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://wpml.org/2016/03/wpml-compatibility-release-wordpress-4-5/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/wpml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel";s:3:"hub";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:4:"info";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"uri";s:4:"wpml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;